This paper deals with the clique-width of graphs, which is a measure of their structural complexity. This topic is closely related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by the cs.DM and cs.DS sub-categories. The paper also presents a polynomial time algorithm for graph isomorphism, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and is covered by the cs.CG and cs.CC sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses techniques from parameterized complexity and algorithm design, which are covered by the cs.LG sub-category.
